  "prompt": "What is the difference between UMTS and 4G?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between UMTS and 4G:\n\nUMTS (3G):\n1. Slower data speeds (384 kbps - 2 Mbps)\n2. Based on WCDMA technology\n3. Introduced around 2001\n4. Voice-centric network\n5. Limited multimedia capabilities\n6. Narrower bandwidth\n7. Less efficient spectrum usage\n\n4G (LTE):\n1. Much faster data speeds (100 Mbps - 1 Gbps)\n2. Uses IP-based packet switching\n3. Introduced around 2009\n4. Data-centric network\n5. Enhanced multimedia and streaming capabilities\n6. Wider bandwidth\n7. More efficient spectrum usage\n8. Lower latency\n9. Better support for mobile internet and applications\n10. Improved network capacity and performance\n\nThe primary differences are in speed, technology, and overall network capabilities, with 4G representing a significant technological advancement over UMTS.",
